or patronizes a group,"},{"type":"text","text":"[frend]"},{"type":"text","text":"cause, or movement)"},{"type":"text","text":"Queen Elizabeth I has quite correctly been called a friend of the arts, because"},{"type":"text","text":"many young artists received her patronage."},{"type":"entry","text":"inconsolable","headword":"inconsolable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj无法慰藉的（incapable of being consoled)，悲痛欲绝的"},{"type":"text","text":"[Inkan'saulabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"In the poem Annabel Lee, the speaker reveals that he is not resigned to the"},{"type":"text","text":"death of his beloved; on the contrary, he is inconsolable,"},{"type":"entry","text":"vaulted","headword":"vaulted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj拱形的"},{"type":"text","text":"['vo:ltrd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"overbear","headword":"overbear"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 压倒(to bring down by superior weight or physical force); 镇压(to domineer"},{"type":"text","text":"[auvar'ber]"},{"type":"text","text":"over);比--更重要，超过（to surpass in importance or cogency)"},{"type":"entry","text":"disconsolate","headword":"disconsolate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 闷闷不乐的，郁郁寡欢的(cheerless, dejected, downcast)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dis'ka:nsalat]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：dis（不）+con（强调）+sol(安慰）+ate→没有安慰的→闷闷不乐的"},{"type":"entry","text":"predatory","headword":"predatory"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 掠夺的(of, relating to, or practicing plunder, pillage, or rapine);食肉的"},{"type":"text","text":"['predato:ri]"},{"type":"text","text":"(predaceous)"},{"type":"text","text":"Aimed at curbing European attempts to seize territory in the Americas, the"},{"type":"text","text":"Monroe Doctrine was a warning to precfatory foreign powers."},{"type":"text","text":"predlatorial, rapacious, raptorial"},{"type":"entry","text":"constituent","headword":"constituent"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.成分(component, element);选区内的选民(a member of a constituency)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'stitfuant]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：con（共同）+sti（看作stat，站）+uent→站在一起投票→选区内的选民"}]},{"number":365,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"slothful","headword":"slothful"},{"type":"text","text":"adfj迟钝的，懒情的(lazy)"},{"type":"text","text":"['slauofl]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：sloth（树懒，在树上生活，行动迟缓）+ful→像树懒一样懒散的→懒"},{"type":"text","text":"情的"},{"type":"text","text":"sluggish"},{"type":"entry","text":"homemade","headword":"homemade"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 自制的， 家里做的(made in the home, on the premises, or by one’s own"},{"type":"text","text":"[haum'meid]"},{"type":"text","text":"efforts)"},{"type":"entry","text":"ribaldry","headword":"ribaldry"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.下流的语言，粗都的幽默（ribald language or humor)"},{"type":"text","text":"['rrbldri]"},{"type":"text","text":"obscenity"},{"type":"entry","text":"well-deserved","headword":"well-deserved"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.当之无愧的：罪有应得的"},{"type":"text","text":"[,weldt'z3:rvd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"tyrannical","headword":"tyrannical"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 暴虐的，残暴的(being or characteristic of a tyrant or tyranny)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tr'raenrkl]"},{"type":"text","text":"despotic, oppressive, tyrannic"},{"type":"entry","text":"grating","headword":"grating"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. (声音)刺耳的(harsh and rasping);恼人的(iritating or annoying)"},{"type":"text","text":"hoarse, raucous"},{"type":"text","text":"['grertin]"},{"type":"entry","text":"behoove","headword":"behoove"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.理应，有必要(to be right or necessary to)"},{"type":"text","text":"[br'hu:v]"},{"type":"entry","text":"specter","headword":"specter"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.鬼怪，幽灵（a ghostly apparition)：缠绕心头的恐惧，凶兆(sth.that haunts or"},{"type":"text","text":"['spektar]"},{"type":"text","text":"perturbs the mind)"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：spect（看）+er→看到而摸不着的东西→鬼怪"},{"type":"text","text":"eidolon, phantasm, phantom, spirit"},{"type":"entry","text":"ferment","headword":"ferment"},{"type":"definiti